The name Presley is an English baby name. In English the meaning of the name Presley is: From the priest's meadow.

Presley Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Priest's meadow Short Info: Priscilla Presley is an American model and singer and was the wife of Elvis Presley "The King of Rock 'n' Roll". Details: Originates from the old English term meaning "from the priest's meadow". Now more usually associated with the 1950s icon Elvis Presley. Gender: For both boy and girl, unisex, transgender, neutral gender Origin: English Religion: Christian Suitable for: Unisex / Gender neutral Hardness: Medium hard to pronounce Uniqueness: It is a common name Short & Easy: Not very short Syllables: 7 Letters and 1 Words
